  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>All new brickwork and works of repair to external plaster shall be completed in reclaimed London Stock bricks in Flemish bond (as detailed in drawing 21) and all mortar and plaster shall be based with lime. No cement -based mortar or plaster shall be used.</p><p><br></p><p>REASON: To safeguard the external appearance and historic fabric of the host building.</p><p><br></p>",
    "<p>The roof extension hereby permitted shall not be occupied until at least one bird box or brick, suitable for swifts, starlings or sparrows, has been installed at roof level in accordance with the manufacturer's specifications.</p><p>The installed bird box / brick, shall thereafter be maintained in accordance with the manufacturer's specifications.</p><p><br></p><p>REASON: To enhance biodiversity at the site and in the area.</p><p><br></p>",
    "<p>The development hereby permitted shall only be carried out and completed strictly in accordance with the submitted plans and documents hereby approved and any other conditions attached to this planning permission.\r\n</p><p><br></p><p>\r\nREASON: To ensure that the development hereby permitted is carried out in full accordance with the plans hereby approved and for the avoidance of doubt.\r\n</p>",
    "<p>The development hereby permitted must be begun not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of this permission.</p><p><br></p><p>\r\n</p><p>\r\nREASON: In order to comply with the provisions of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).</p><p>\r\n</p>",
    "<p>All new and replacement double glazed windows shall have a maximum glazing profile of 12mm (4mm glass, 4mm gap, 4mm glass) and shall have integral glazing bars.</p><p><br></p><p>REASON: To safeguard the historic fabric and external appearance of the host building.<br></p>"
